Here is a complete map of how GitHub org/account avatars are displayed in this codebase.

---

## Pattern Examples: GitHub Organization Avatar Display

### Pattern 1: Avatar in Installation Dropdown (SelectItem)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/sources/new/_components/provider-source-item.tsx:311–330`
**Used for**: Showing each GitHub installation's org avatar next to its name in a `<Select>` dropdown when `installationMode === "multi"`.

```tsx
{installations.map((inst) => (
  <SelectItem key={inst.id} value={inst.id}>
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      {inst.avatarUrl ? (
        <Image
          alt=""
          className="rounded-full"
          height={16}
          src={inst.avatarUrl}
          width={16}
        />
      ) : (
        <Icon className="h-4 w-4" />
      )}
      {inst.label}
    </div>
  </SelectItem>
))}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses Next.js `Image` component (not a plain `<img>` tag)
- Falls back to the provider `Icon` component when `avatarUrl` is null/undefined
- 16×16px, `rounded-full` class
- `alt=""` (decorative image)
- `inst.label` is the GitHub org login name (e.g. `acme-corp`)

---

### Pattern 2: NormalizedInstallation shape (the data type)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-providers/src/provider/resource-picker.ts:12–17`

```ts
export interface NormalizedInstallation {
  readonly avatarUrl?: string | null;
  readonly externalId: string;
  readonly id: string;
  readonly label: string;
}
```

`avatarUrl` is always optional/nullable. The UI's conditional check `{inst.avatarUrl ? <Image ...> : <Icon ...>}` directly mirrors this type.

---

### Pattern 3: Mapping GitHub API `avatar_url` → `avatarUrl`
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-providers/src/providers/github/index.ts:288–308`

```ts
enrichInstallation: async (executeApi, inst) => {
  try {
    const res = await executeApi({
      endpointId: "get-app-installation",
      pathParams: { installation_id: inst.externalId },
    });
    const data = githubAppInstallationSchema.parse(res.data);
    return {
      id: inst.id,
      externalId: inst.externalId,
      label: data.account?.login ?? inst.externalId,
      avatarUrl: data.account?.avatar_url ?? null,   // ← snake_case → camelCase
    };
  } catch {
    return {
      id: inst.id,
      externalId: inst.externalId,
      label: inst.externalId,
      avatarUrl: null,                               // ← null fallback
    };
  }
},
```

The raw GitHub API schema (`githubAppInstallationSchema`) defines `avatar_url: z.string().optional()` at `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-providers/src/providers/github/api.ts:66–67`.

---

### Pattern 4: tRPC `listInstallations` procedure (server side)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/app/src/router/org/connections.ts:653–709`

Queries `gatewayInstallations` for active installations belonging to the org, then calls `enrichInstallation` for each (via platform proxy), and returns `{ installationMode, resourceLabel, installations: NormalizedInstallation[] }`. The `avatarUrl` field comes back as part of each `NormalizedInstallation` in that array.

---

### Pattern 5: Next.js image domain allowlist
